- Yeah. What are you waiting for?

303
00:21:48,180 --> 00:21:49,980
Wait!

304
00:21:49,980 --> 00:21:51,900
What is it?

305
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:24,960
You're such a hassle.

306
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:27,180
I told you to go home, but you didn't listen.

307
00:22:27,180 --> 00:22:30,240
Watphlus never leave each other.

308
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:32,240
Because you're so cute.

309
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:33,920
Huh?

310
00:22:36,860 --> 00:22:38,740
All done.

311
00:22:40,680 --> 00:22:43,640
It's okay. I'll pay.

312
00:22:50,760 --> 00:22:52,800
I'm touched.

313
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:18,340
Go ahead. Your friends have been waiting too long.

314
00:23:18,340 --> 00:23:21,220
We're good. No rush.

315
00:23:21,220 --> 00:23:23,360
Let's make sure that the bike is good to go.

316
00:23:42,420 --> 00:23:45,040
Go home safely.

317
00:23:45,040 --> 00:23:46,940
Thank you.

318
00:24:06,940 --> 00:24:10,580
Just wait and see. He's going to complain about something.

319
00:24:10,580 --> 00:24:11,940
Damn it!

320
00:24:11,940 --> 00:24:14,160
It's so difficult to put on! So troublesome.

321
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:18,400
There you go. That's the real Noey Watphlu.

322
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:21,100
Just as I thought.

323
00:24:28,860 --> 00:24:30,560
Here.

324
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:42,160
Even though he is a delinquent,

325
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:44,860
he still needs someone to take care of him.

326
00:24:48,140 --> 00:24:50,740
He's such a pain in the ass…

327
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:16,560
Drive safely, Noey.

328
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:25,780
Hey, you! Yes, you.

329
00:25:25,780 --> 00:25:27,000
Are you going with us?

330
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,020
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

331
00:25:29,020 --> 00:25:31,360
Come on, you'll see each other again.

332
00:25:35,380 --> 00:25:37,180
- Go!
- Wait a second.

333
00:25:37,180 --> 00:25:38,880
Go!

334
00:25:45,740 --> 00:25:48,600
Hey. Spill it.

335
00:25:50,020 --> 00:25:51,520
Here.

336
00:25:52,340 --> 00:25:54,400
Oh, you meant spilling the tea?

337
00:25:55,620 --> 00:25:57,420
My bad.

338
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:01,040
The thing is…

339
00:26:22,420 --> 00:26:24,800
I see. My gosh.

340
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:26,783
But that's it?

341
00:26:26,783 --> 00:26:29,663
Nothing else?

342
00:26:29,663 --> 00:26:31,080
What exactly do you mean?

343
00:26:31,080 --> 00:26:35,750
Well, between you and that kid.

344
00:26:35,750 --> 00:26:38,140
Or maybe I should pursue you?

345
00:26:38,140 --> 00:26:39,780
Can you teach me about Thi instead?

346
00:26:39,780 --> 00:26:42,360
You have to endure it as a wife.

347
00:26:43,300 --> 00:26:45,000
There's nothing going on!

348
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:48,100
That's all.

349
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:53,840
So you weren't threatened or beaten up? Or…

350
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:55,340
No!

351
00:26:55,340 --> 00:26:59,620
There's nothing else. I told you everything.

352
00:26:59,620 --> 00:27:02,720
That's all. Really.

353
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:05,400
You guys are so nosy.

354
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:06,940
Cheers!

355
00:27:06,940 --> 00:27:08,300
Let's cheers!

356
00:27:08,300 --> 00:27:11,224
Cheers to what? Your glass is empty.

357
00:27:14,780 --> 00:27:18,380
Okay. I'm ready.

358
00:27:20,940 --> 00:27:24,120
Open the lid first!

359
00:27:24,120 --> 00:27:26,320
That was a joke.

360
00:27:26,320 --> 00:27:30,540
Hey, Thi, if there's something going on, you can tell us.

361
00:27:30,540 --> 00:27:35,640
No, no way. You're thinking too much.

362
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:39,060
Everything is perfectly normal.

363
00:27:39,060 --> 00:27:41,920
- But you're acting weird.
- Yeah.

364
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:43,440
I have mine.

365
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:46,180
- What about you?
- No, I'm good.

366
00:27:46,180 --> 00:27:47,940
What's wrong with you?

367
00:27:47,940 --> 00:27:50,200
Drink up.

368
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:52,760
Yeah, my throat is pretty dry.

369
00:27:57,380 --> 00:27:59,040
You want more?

370
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:02,340
Number two: Help them with something they can't do.

371
00:28:02,340 --> 00:28:04,920
I took him to fight with another gang.

372
00:28:08,420 --> 00:28:11,480
Today, I made him misbehave.

373
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:14,000
I'm sure he was impressed.

374
00:28:18,900 --> 00:28:22,420
Oh, I forgot to ask about my score.

375
00:28:23,540 --> 00:28:25,260
What are you smiling about?

376
00:28:25,260 --> 00:28:28,060
Did your dad make you laugh or something?

377
00:28:29,780 --> 00:28:31,360
Auntie Tim.

378
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:32,700
What?

379
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:34,500
Can you buy me a helmet?

380
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:37,380
Huh? What did you say?

381
00:28:37,940 --> 00:28:40,000
Am I dreaming?

382
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:43,360
My son asked me to buy him a helmet.

383
00:28:45,420 --> 00:28:50,400
And one more thing. Your motorbike was out of gas.

384
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:54,300
But it turned out to be a good thing.

385
00:28:54,300 --> 00:28:57,240
I got to talk to him longer.

386
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:07,660
What's with you?

387
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:10,480
And did you fill up the tank?

388
00:29:10,480 --> 00:29:13,400
- What color do you want for a helmet?
- Any color is fine!

389
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:15,994
- Just use your dad's old helmet then!
- Fine.

390
00:29:15,994 --> 00:29:19,660
Okay! So did you fill up the tank? You still haven't answered me.

391
00:29:19,660 --> 00:29:21,700
Mom, you woke me up!

392
00:29:21,700 --> 00:29:26,220
- What are you two yelling about?
- Noey didn't answer me about the gas!

393
00:29:26,220 --> 00:29:29,400
- So did you fill up the tank for Mom or not?
- It's done already.

394
00:29:29,400 --> 00:29:33,320
- All right, Mom? I'm going back to sleep!
- That's all. Done!

395
00:29:35,380 --> 00:29:37,940
The next move…

396
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:41,300
will probably have to wait until the school break.

397
00:29:43,960 --> 00:29:46,300
May all the students of Watphlu.

398
00:29:46,300 --> 00:29:50,180
focus and concentrate during your exams.

399
00:29:50,180 --> 00:29:54,740
No copying and no cheating. These will become a bad habit.

400
00:29:54,740 --> 00:29:56,840
Us teachers believe that if our students

401
00:29:56,840 --> 00:30:01,000
are determined, everyone will do well on the exams.

402
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,600
Good luck to everyone.

403
00:30:02,600 --> 00:30:07,580
May all of you get A's across the board.

404
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:15,260
Finally, it's time for our boss to…

405
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:19,120
Be on school break!

406
00:30:21,020 --> 00:30:23,800
Yeah!

407
00:30:23,800 --> 00:30:28,480
Whatever it is. As of now,

408
00:30:29,740 --> 00:30:32,440
Watphlu has officially finished tenth grade.

409
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:34,260
Way too awesome.

410
00:30:34,260 --> 00:30:36,900
I already told you that I'm not available.

411
00:30:36,900 --> 00:30:39,660
And I have to set up a volunteer camp.

412
00:30:39,660 --> 00:30:43,099
What volunteer camp? Just do it after our trip.

413
00:30:43,099 --> 00:30:44,161
- No can do.
- You're being so difficult.

414
00:30:44,161 --> 00:30:45,360
- No can do.
- You're being so difficult.

415
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:48,140
Who's the one being difficult?

416
00:30:48,140 --> 00:30:52,200
Hey, I asked you to go even before my final exams.

417
00:30:54,900 --> 00:30:56,580
It's me, Thi.

418
00:30:56,580 --> 00:31:01,500
Final exams are approaching, and I might disappear from you for a while.

419
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:05,020
Don't miss me too much. But if you do, just call me.

420
00:31:05,020 --> 00:31:10,100
If you can't reach me, you can just call Nid Nhoi.

421
00:31:10,100 --> 00:31:12,380
Oh, and…

422
00:31:12,380 --> 00:31:14,040
after the finals, I will take you on a trip to relax.

423
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:15,600
after the finals, I will take you on a trip to relax.

424
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:21,220
Number five... oh! Never mind. It was nothing.

425
00:31:21,220 --> 00:31:24,980
I was talking about the exam.

426
00:31:24,980 --> 00:31:27,540
But I didn't agree to it.

427
00:31:27,540 --> 00:31:31,960
But you didn't tell me that you weren't going either.

428
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:33,980
You're so sly, Noey.

429
00:31:33,980 --> 00:31:37,260
You've fallen right into my trap, Thi.

430
00:31:45,540 --> 00:31:47,340
Thank you.

431
00:31:56,460 --> 00:31:58,540
I don't like him.

432
00:31:58,540 --> 00:32:01,220
I'm going to smack him the next time I see him.

433
00:32:01,220 --> 00:32:03,700
Don't act like a delinquent here.

434
00:32:04,500 --> 00:32:08,420
Why not? Then go on a trip with me first.

435
00:32:08,420 --> 00:32:10,300
What does it have to do with this?

436
00:32:10,300 --> 00:32:14,180
Anything can be related.

437
00:32:14,180 --> 00:32:17,060
We may be related in some way in our past lives.

438
00:32:17,060 --> 00:32:19,240
You never know.

439
00:32:23,220 --> 00:32:25,320
So you're going. Right?

440
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:28,100
Go with me, please?

441
00:32:28,100 --> 00:32:30,340
I put a lot of effort into studying for the finals just for you.

442
00:32:30,340 --> 00:32:32,020
Think about that.

443
00:32:44,580 --> 00:32:46,340
Give it to me.

444
00:32:56,380 --> 00:33:00,600
Hold on, hold on. What's going on?

445
00:33:01,900 --> 00:33:03,960
Nothing.

446
00:33:08,700 --> 00:33:11,160
Noey, give it back to him.

447
00:33:17,780 --> 00:33:21,160
Oh, this is Phayu. He's my friend. Do you remember him?

448
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:23,721
I invited him to the volunteer camp.

449
00:33:23,721 --> 00:33:25,380
Perfect timing. Now you guys get to know each other.

450
00:33:25,380 --> 00:33:26,860
How's it going?

451
00:33:26,860 --> 00:33:28,100
Hi.

452
00:33:28,100 --> 00:33:30,180
No one wants to know you.

453
00:33:40,440 --> 00:33:42,880
Please don't mind him.

454
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:46,780
He's just upset about final exams.

455
00:33:46,780 --> 00:33:48,020
Thi.

456
00:33:48,020 --> 00:33:50,340
You're okay. Right?

457
00:33:50,340 --> 00:33:55,020
I'm okay. I'll clear things up with him.

458
00:33:55,020 --> 00:33:59,000
All right then. Let's go play basketball.

459
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:08,020
Noey, you have to calm down.

460
00:34:08,020 --> 00:34:10,300
You can't go around picking fights whenever and wherever you go.

461
00:34:10,300 --> 00:34:12,180
Just sometimes.

462
00:34:12,180 --> 00:34:15,100
Okay. Whatever you say.

463
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:17,700
I've been busy lately.

464
00:34:17,700 --> 00:34:19,500
I don't have the time to argue with you.

465
00:34:19,500 --> 00:34:21,260
Then I'll help.

466
00:34:21,260 --> 00:34:24,500
What are you going to do? A volunteer camp?

467
00:34:24,500 --> 00:34:26,860
I'm in. I'll go.

468
00:34:26,860 --> 00:34:28,540
I will help you.

469
00:34:28,540 --> 00:34:31,400
We can take a rain check on our trip for now.

470
00:34:36,980 --> 00:34:40,820
This time, I want to focus on recreational activities as well.

471
00:34:40,820 --> 00:34:42,500
So the kids can have some fun

472
00:34:42,500 --> 00:34:46,220
and not stress about studying during school break.

473
00:34:50,740 --> 00:34:52,700
Regarding the equipment, we'll let

474
00:34:52,700 --> 00:34:56,040
our new members, Phum and Ann, explain in detail.

475
00:34:56,040 --> 00:34:57,481
Hello. I'm Phum.

476
00:34:57,481 --> 00:34:59,020
I'm Ann.

477
00:34:59,020 --> 00:35:02,980
First off, about school supplies,

478
00:35:02,980 --> 00:35:05,540
there are pencils, notebooks, and pens.

479
00:35:05,540 --> 00:35:09,360
We've collected enough of these items through donations.

480
00:35:10,780 --> 00:35:14,260
You go ahead and do your work. Don't mind me.

481
00:35:14,260 --> 00:35:16,970
I'm going to sit here quietly.

482
00:35:16,970 --> 00:35:19,380
No need to worry about me.

483
00:35:21,860 --> 00:35:23,640
Thanks.

484
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:27,800
Anything for you, always.

485
00:35:47,740 --> 00:35:50,780
Is there anything you want to add?

486
00:35:50,780 --> 00:35:56,140
Because this year's camp is very close, unlike previous years that we went out of town.

487
00:35:56,140 --> 00:36:01,220
If you're thinking about bringing something, but not sure if it's convenient or not.

488
00:36:01,220 --> 00:36:02,980
Don't think too much. Just bring it along.

489
00:36:02,980 --> 00:36:05,720
Commuting there is very convenient. Don't worry.

490
00:36:05,720 --> 00:36:10,000
If anyone needs anything, just ask me.

491
00:36:19,380 --> 00:36:23,280
Well, it's weird but in a good way. The camp is so close.

492
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:26,260
- You're right. We usually go out of town.
- Yeah.

493
00:36:26,260 --> 00:36:30,420
This is good. We can even sneak back home for a nap.

494
00:36:30,420 --> 00:36:34,580
Hey, please don't! Sleeping together is much more fun.

495
00:36:34,580 --> 00:36:38,300
That's right. We'd better sleep together. Break the routine.

496
00:36:43,300 --> 00:36:45,060
Where do you want to set up?

497
00:36:45,060 --> 00:36:47,040
I'll do it for you.

498
00:36:48,380 --> 00:36:50,060
Set up?

499
00:36:50,060 --> 00:36:52,820
Set up your tent, Dummy.

500
00:36:57,380 --> 00:36:58,820
Anywhere is fine.

501
00:36:58,820 --> 00:37:01,060
He's quite aggressive. What made him so worked up?

502
00:37:01,060 --> 00:37:05,440
Then I'll choose the spot where I want to sleep.

503
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:13,040
What's with him?

504
00:37:13,040 --> 00:37:14,340
Let's go.

505
00:37:14,340 --> 00:37:17,120
- Go, go, go.
- Go, Thi, go.

506
00:37:25,340 --> 00:37:28,060
This used to be an old cemetery.

507
00:37:28,060 --> 00:37:29,540
That spot is taken.

508
00:37:29,540 --> 00:37:33,880
If you take that spot, you're in for something good.

509
00:37:42,240 --> 00:37:45,620
Woah! That spot is even worse.

510
00:37:45,620 --> 00:37:49,020
Just stepping on it, you'll be haunted all the way home.

511
00:37:49,020 --> 00:37:50,820
It's up to you.

512
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:10,280
Come here.

513
00:38:15,020 --> 00:38:16,760
Help me with this.

514
00:38:20,820 --> 00:38:24,060
Here, here. I'll do it myself.

515
00:38:24,060 --> 00:38:26,260
We should just order food from Auntie Tim's place.

516
00:38:26,260 --> 00:38:28,520
What do you think?

517
00:38:34,260 --> 00:38:36,280
Let me go and help them.

518
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:41,380
Noey, don't!

519
00:38:41,380 --> 00:38:46,140
- Noey!
- Step aside. If you want some good food, let me cook.

520
00:38:54,920 --> 00:38:56,680
What's going on?

521
00:38:57,400 --> 00:39:00,600
- Just wait. Be patient. Just eat your meatballs.
- Oh no!

522
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:01,820
Help me stir the pot.

523
00:39:01,820 --> 00:39:05,060
Noey Watphlu's cooking.

524
00:39:05,060 --> 00:39:07,180
Hey.

525
00:39:07,180 --> 00:39:09,060
What?

526
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:12,900
Oh my!

527
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:15,980
You said you like something sweet.

528
00:39:23,400 --> 00:39:26,100
Yeah! That is Noey's cooking!

529
00:39:33,420 --> 00:39:35,260
It's pretty good.

530
00:39:36,300 --> 00:39:39,700
What? What's wrong with your tongue?

531
00:39:42,540 --> 00:39:45,060
I'm glad you like it, Thi.

532
00:39:45,060 --> 00:39:49,220
His cooking skills never fail me.

533
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:51,900
Since I was born, I tried his cooking once,

534
00:39:51,900 --> 00:39:54,220
and it's salty to this day.

535
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:56,900
- You think it's good?
